dc:description: At the center of the interior, within and incised circle, the stamp MAND in a rectangle, Mand(uili). Mandilus was a potter of La Graufesenque, active during the period from Claudous through Vespasian.
Gazda: Red gloss cup. Clay, fabric of south Gaul.
